      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "RINSED THE LOT (6) was in the minor money with a good 19.87, finishing second in a Free For All at this track last start. Rates a top chance again if runs up to latest. STAR ASSASSIN (7) has some solid form under his belt and proved too classy last time to win by 2.25 lengths at this track in a handy 19.84 beating Black Raspberry. Form from his last run is proving to be solid. Makes plenty of appeal if runs up to latest. SOMEONE'S IDEA (1) comes off an average run last start when fifth at Q Parklands over 520m behind Non Stop Whiskey (30.47) in a Grade 5. Some good form is emerging from her last run. Better than last start and can bounce back. BROOKERS ROAD (4) has strong credentials over this journey.",
